## Checklist — never ship a filter without this

- [ ] Backend `FilterSet` has the method implemented and added to `fields`
- [ ] `ViewSet` has `filterset_class` set
- [ ] Manually tested with `curl` or browser before writing frontend
- [ ] Query builder passes the param — no `void params.xxx`
- [ ] TypeScript type includes the new param
- [ ] Page reads the URL param and passes it to the fetch function
- [ ] UI toggle updates the URL param (not local state)
- [ ] If using load-more pagination: Route Handler also forwards the param
